t last after several enormous seconds of confusion and despair and shuffled this way and that Impatiently while the cloakroom attendant, like a somnambulist, looked for his things.... He was the first to get dressed and the first to go out and his wife swiftly followed him, pulling her moleskin coat together as she went. Only in the car did Luzhin begin to breathe freely, and his expression of distracted sullenness gave way to a guilty half-smile. 'Dear Luzhin met a nasty person,' said his wife,